Name: molasses, from sugar beet, to generic market for energy feed | energy feed, gross | EN15804GD, U
Category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/108:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds/1080:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds
Description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/9957/documentation

This is a linking activity that converts molasses, from sugar beet into gross energy for the feed market and protein, 100% crude for the feed market.;The naming of the dataset is based on the feed nomenclature system of the National Research Council (USA).  Products with less than 20 percent of protein are classified as energy feeds. Products with more than 20 percent of protein are classified as protein feeds.

The activity starts with the reception of molasses, from sugar beet

The activity ends with the conversion of molasses, from sugar beet into gross energy and crude protein
